            <head>THE ORDEAL</head>
            <lg part="N" org="uniform" sample="complete">
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">Ho! my brother,</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">Pass me not by so scornfully</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">I’m doing this living of being black,</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">Perhaps I bear your own life-pack,</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">And heavy, heavy is the load</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">That bends my body to the road.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg part="N" org="uniform" sample="complete">
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">But I have kept a smile for fate,</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">I neither cry, nor cringe, nor hate,</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">Intrepidly, I strive to bear</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">This handicap. The planets wear</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">The Maker’s imprint, and with mine</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">I swing into their rhythmic line;</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">I ask—only for destiny,</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">Mine, not thine.</l>
            </lg>
            <byline>-Georgia Douglas Johnson</byline>
         </div>
